>>>>>>>>>>> Thank you for reaching out to us about hosting your Y2K-themed
>>>>>>>>>>> end-of-the-year party at Moonlight Lounge on November 28, 2024. We're
>>>>>>>>>>> excited to let you know that our space is available for your event on that
>>>>>>>>>>> date.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> As the event falls on a Thursday, our rental rate for the
>>>>>>>>>>> Moonlight Lounge would be $125 per hour, with a minimum spending
>>>>>>>>>>> requirement of $500. Since you mentioned approximately 120 guests, please
>>>>>>>>>>> note that our maximum capacity is 194, but we comfortably accommodate 150
>>>>>>>>>>> guests.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> Our space comes equipped with a dancefloor, professional sound
>>>>>>>>>>> system with karaoke, party lights, smoke machine, private bar staffed with
>>>>>>>>>>> two bartenders, and private washrooms. You'll also have access to our full
>>>>>>>>>>> sound system, allowing you to connect your own music via Bluetooth or use a
>>>>>>>>>>> provided tablet with a Spotify playlist. Additionally, we have a TV for
>>>>>>>>>>> use, which can be connected via HDMI port.
>>>>>>>>>>>
>>>>>>>>>>> If you have any further questions or would like to proceed with
>>>>>>>>>>> booking, please don't hesitate to reach out to us. We'd be happy to discuss
>>>>>>>>>>> more details.

>>>>>>>>>>> 647-692-4768

Thank you for reaching out to us about hosting your Y2K-themed end-of-the-year party at Moonlight Lounge on November 28, 2024. We're excited to let you know that our space is available for your event on that date.

As the event falls on a Thursday, our rental rate for the Moonlight Lounge would be $125 per hour, with a minimum spending requirement of $500. Since you mentioned approximately 120 guests, please note that our maximum capacity is 194, but we comfortably accommodate 150 guests.

Our space comes equipped with a dancefloor, professional sound system with karaoke, party lights, smoke machine, private bar staffed with two bartenders, and private washrooms. You'll also have access to our full sound system, allowing you to connect your own music via Bluetooth or use a provided tablet with a Spotify playlist. Additionally, we have a TV for use, which can be connected via HDMI port.

If you have any further questions or would like to proceed with booking, please don't hesitate to reach out to us. We'd be happy to discuss more details.

Best regards,

Hi Sarah,

Happy Friday! Did you anticipate ordering any of our catering or drink packages? Here they are in case we didn't share:

For food, we can offer light appetizers for $6 per person. This includes loaded nachos, jalapeno poppers, fries and pizzadilla. If you want to do two tacos+appetizers per person, we can do it for $16 per person. You can choose between 4-6 tacos and apps and can see the full menu here: eattaco.ca/menu. If you want a full plated buffet catering, it would be $30 per person. I've attached the plated buffet menu for reference. Let us know if you have any questions

If you'd like to provide drinks for your guests, you can purchase drink tickets at $8 each + tax & gratuity which covers all our drinks except for the cocktails. Or, you can set a budget for open bar and people can order from the open bar until that limit is reached.

TacoTaco Events Team

Hey Sandra!

 

Sorry, I misread your email. The $750 is the min spend on top of the rental. If you want to do a min spend only option, it would be $1750 or about $35 per person. For this, we’d ask for a deposit of $800 and will return it if the minimum spend is hit. We also partially return it if you miss the min spend. Here is the wording from the contract:

 

To host an event, a deposit of $800 is required along with a minimum spend of $1750 for the night. If the minimum spend requirement is met, the full deposit amount will be refunded. However, if the spend falls below the minimum requirement, the deposit will be forfeited in proportion to the amount by which the spend falls short.

Good morning,

My name is Andrew Tribe and I am the Artistic Director of the Mainstage
Theatre Company in Toronto. We are a not-for-profit youth theatre company
that mounts two productions per year in Toronto with youth ages 11 - 21.

We are looking to host a fundraiser at the end of our year to celebrate the
year's accomplishments and look towards the future. We also hope we can
have a few of our students perform some songs (with keyboard
accompaniment). Your space came recommended by one of our staff members! :)

Our tentative dates would be either the evening of Sunday, June 1, 2025 or
Sunday, June 8, 2025.

We would be interested in the Moonlight Lounge space (194).

What can you share about food? Is the space accessible for all ages? What
is the approximate cost?

Our company is operated by a Board of Directors, so as much info you can
provide, I can relay it back to them.

Thank you so much!

Warmly,
Andrew.

Oh I'm so sorry! You're looking at November 26th - I was looking at the wrong day. Yes it is available.  The Moonlight Lounge is available that day, and the cost to rent it is $125/hr with a minimum spend of $750 across food and drinks. The rental comes with the use of our sound system (including karaoke), bartending staff, party lights, a fully stocked bar and clean up.

For food, we can offer light appetizers for $6 per person. This includes loaded nachos, jalapeno poppers, fries and pizzadilla. If you want to do two tacos+appetizers per person, we can do it for $16 per person. You can choose between 4-6 tacos and apps and can see the full menu here: eattaco.ca/menu<http://eattaco.ca/menu>. Thank you for reaching out to us about hosting your Y2K-themed end-of-the-year party at Moonlight Lounge on November 28, 2024. We're excited to let you know that our space is available for your event on that date.

As the event falls on a Thursday, our rental rate for the Moonlight Lounge would be $125 per hour, with a minimum spending requirement of $500. Since you mentioned approximately 120 guests, please note that our maximum capacity is 194, but we comfortably accommodate 150 guests.

Our space comes equipped with a dancefloor, professional sound system with karaoke, party lights, smoke machine, private bar staffed with two bartenders, and private washrooms. You'll also have access to our full sound system, allowing you to connect your own music via Bluetooth or use a provided tablet with a Spotify playlist. Additionally, we have a TV for use, which can be connected via HDMI port.

If you have any further questions or would like to proceed with booking, please don't hesitate to reach out to us. We'd be happy to discuss more details.

Best regards,
TacoTaco Events Team

Sent: Friday, October 25, 2024 at 08:24:39 PM EDT
Subject: Fw: New Event Inquiry


Thank you for reaching out to us about hosting your Y2K-themed end-of-the-year party at Moonlight Lounge on November 28, 2024. We're excited to let you know that our space is available for your event on that date.

As the event falls on a Thursday, our rental rate for the Moonlight Lounge would be $125 per hour, with a minimum spending requirement of $500. Since you mentioned approximately 120 guests, please note that our maximum capacity is 194, but we comfortably accommodate 150 guests.

Our space comes equipped with a dancefloor, professional sound system with karaoke, party lights, smoke machine, private bar staffed with two bartenders, and private washrooms. You'll also have access to our full sound system, allowing you to connect your own music via Bluetooth or use a provided tablet with a Spotify playlist. Additionally, we have a TV for use, which can be connected via HDMI port.

If you have any further questions or would like to proceed with booking, please don't hesitate to reach out to us. We'd be happy to discuss more details.

Best regards,
TacoTaco Events Team
647-692-4768

Thank you for reaching out to us about hosting your Y2K-themed end-of-the-year party at Moonlight Lounge on November 28, 2024. We're excited to let you know that our space is available for your event on that date.

As the event falls on a Thursday, our rental rate for the Moonlight Lounge would be $125 per hour, with a minimum spending requirement of $500. Since you mentioned approximately 120 guests, please note that our maximum capacity is 194, but we comfortably accommodate 150 guests.

Our space comes equipped with a dancefloor, professional sound system with karaoke, party lights, smoke machine, private bar staffed with two bartenders, and private washrooms. You'll also have access to our full sound system, allowing you to connect your own music via Bluetooth or use a provided tablet with a Spotify playlist. Additionally, we have a TV for use, which can be connected via HDMI port.

If you have any further questions or would like to proceed with booking, please don't hesitate to reach out to us. We'd be happy to discuss more details.

Best regards,

Hey Sandra!

 

Sorry, I misread your email. The $750 is the min spend on top of the rental. If you want to do a min spend only option, it would be $1750 or about $35 per person. For this, we’d ask for a deposit of $800 and will return it if the minimum spend is hit. We also partially return it if you miss the min spend. Here is the wording from the contract:

 

To host an event, a deposit of $800 is required along with a minimum spend of $1750 for the night. If the minimum spend requirement is met, the full deposit amount will be refunded. However, if the spend falls below the minimum requirement, the deposit will be forfeited in proportion to the amount by which the spend falls short.

subject: Inquiry on Event Space Rental for a Cannabis Industry Event
text:
Hi there,

I hope this message finds you well. I’m reaching out to explore the
possibility of renting your space for a cannabis-related event on
January 17th.

We’re an independent, women-owned cannabis store based in Pickering,
dedicated to showcasing new and legal products released through the Ontario
Cannabis Store (OCS) each quarter. Our events bring together a diverse
audience, including licensed producers, other legal retailers, influencers,
and even members of political organizations. Our most recent event, held on
October 7th at DZO Viet Eatery, was a great success and enjoyed positive
community and industry engagement.

I’d love the opportunity to discuss the feasibility of hosting a future
event at your venue and to explore how we might work together to create a
unique experience for attendees.

Please let me know if we could schedule a time to discuss this further.

Thanks,
*Kira Jissan*
*E-Comm & Marketing Manager*
*Montrose Cannabis*
kira@montrosecannabis.ca
*905-239-5300*
html:
Hi there,

I hope this message finds you well. I’m reaching out to explore the possibility of renting your space for a cannabis-related event on January 17th.

We’re an independent, women-owned cannabis store based in Pickering, dedicated to showcasing new and legal products released through the Ontario Cannabis Store (OCS) each quarter. Our events bring together a diverse audience, including licensed producers, other legal retailers, influencers, and even members of political organizations. Our most recent event, held on October 7th at DZO Viet Eatery, was a great success and enjoyed positive community and industry engagement.

I’d love the opportunity to discuss the feasibility of hosting a future event at your venue and to explore how we might work together to create a unique experience for attendees.

Please let me know if we could schedule a time to discuss this further.

Thanks,

Kira Jissan
